{"questionId":"5275190","questionHtml":"<p>Two resistors of equal resistance R are connected with two cells of emf <em>ε</em> and 2<em>ε</em>. Both cells have negligible internal resistance.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/5bd004197db7ef1b60343f0ca2b321f90d2bdad6.png\"></p>\n<p>What is the current in the resistor labelled X?</p>\n<p><br>A.&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>ε</mi><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>R</mi></mrow></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>B.&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>ε</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>R</mi></mrow></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>C.&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>ε</mi><mi>R</mi></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>D.&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>ε</mi></mrow><mi>R</mi></mfrac></math></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>C</p>","meta":{"questionId":"5275190","referenceCode":"23M.1.SL.TZ2.20","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"Two resistors of equal resistance R are connected with two cells of emf ε and 2ε. Both cells have negligible internal resistance. What is the current in the resistor labelled X? A.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"20","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Option A: Relativity","Option A: Relativity","Option A: Relativity (Core topics)","A.1 – The beginnings of relativity","Option A: Relativity","Option A: Relativity (Core topics)"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}